            <p xml:lang="en" n="7">Good-evening,

            <name type="person">
                <choice>
                 <abbr type="title">Mrs.</abbr>
                </choice>
            McNab</name>
            ," she would say.She had a plesant way with her. 
            The girls all liked her. But dear, many things had changed since then
            (she shut the drawer); many families had lost thier dearest. So she was dead
             </p>

          
            <p xml:lang="en" n="7">and 

            <name type="person">
                <choice>
                 <abbr type="title">Mr.</abbr>
                </choice>
            Andrew</name>
            killed;
             </p>


             <p xml:lang="en" n="7">and 

            <name type="person">
                <choice>
                 <abbr type="title">Dr.</abbr>
                </choice>
            Prue</name>
            dead too, they said, with her first baby; but every one had lost
            some one these years. Prices had gone up shamefully, and didnt come down again 
            neither. She could well remember her in her grey cloak;
             </p>

           

                

